  "standardRef": "AI-STD-014",
  "deviationSummary": "AI-STD-014 requires all LLM API calls to be routed through the corporate API gateway (gw.example.com) for PII scrubbing, rate limiting, and cost attribution. VoiceAssist cannot comply because the gateway adds 85-110 ms of round-trip overhead, causing the end-to-end voice response latency to exceed the 200 ms SLO required for natural conversational pacing.",
  "businessJustification": "VoiceAssist serves 120,000 daily active users on the customer support line. Latency above 200 ms causes measurable user disengagement: A/B tests show a 23% increase in call abandonment at 250 ms vs 180 ms. Compliance with AI-STD-014 via the current gateway path would push P95 latency to ~290 ms, exceeding the SLO and projecting to a 27,000 user/day abandonment increase.",
  "riskAssessment": {
    "likelihood": "medium",
    "impact": "high",
    "residualRisk": "medium",
    "riskNarrative": "Bypassing the gateway removes PII scrubbing from the API call path. User voice transcripts may contain names, account numbers, or health information. The primary risk is inadvertent transmission of PII to the model provider. Compensating control (client-side redaction) reduces this risk materially but cannot guarantee 100% coverage of novel PII patterns."
  },
  "compensatingControls": [
    {
      "control": "Client-side PII redaction using Microsoft Presidio applied to transcripts before API call. Covers 18 PII entity types including names, phone numbers, SSNs, and account numbers.",
      "owner": "Priya Sharma",
      "implementedDate": "2026-07-01"
    },
